# orchestrator-core — Java IPC engine

## Entry points
- `dev/safra/orchestrator/core/Main.java` — stdin loop, dispatches to CoreRuntime
- `dev/safra/orchestrator/core/runtime/CoreRuntime.java` — method switch (IPC contract)

## Packages
| Package | Responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `core` | Main, Args, Json |
| `core.ipc` | IpcRequest/Response/Event, IpcParams, IpcEventEmitter |
| `core.runtime` | Application services: managers, scanners, configurators |
| `model` | Domain: Workspace (aggregate), ServiceDefinition, ServiceView (read model), Container |
| `process` | OS/process infrastructure |

## Persistence (`--stateDir`)
- `workspace.json` — roots, services, containers, removedServices
- `runtime.json` — per-service pid, status, timestamps

## Critical rules
- Container delete never removes services — only clears containerIds
- scanRoots merges containerIds by service name; cleans stale container refs
- removedServices excluded from scan; importRootAndScan clears the set
- Ports from application.properties/yml; JS customPort only when portStrategy=CLI
- listServices re-reads package.json for scripts/port/strategy sync

## IPC
Full method list: repo `docs/reference/IPC.md`. Flow diagrams: `docs/integration/INTEGRATION.md`.

## Build
```bash
mvn -q -DskipTests compile    # quick check
mvn clean package -DskipTests # standalone JAR → copy to desktop src-tauri/
```

## Key classes
WorkspaceManager, ServiceManager, ServiceConfigurator, ServiceViewMapper, ContainerManager, LogManager, ProjectScanner, JsProjectScanner, PhpProjectScanner, DevServerPortDetector, ProcessManager, JavaVersionDetector, WorkspaceDefinitionSync, StateStore
